The multivariate ANOVA (MANOVA) of vegetative and reproductive traits in the control common garden indicated a significant difference between the native and introduced ranges (
 p < 0.05; 
 Supplemental Table 4). The difference between the ranges in phenotypes was significant when CLIMPC1 or CLIMPC2 were included as covariates in the analysis (and when they were excluded), and neither climate variable was significantly associated with the multivariate phenotype (
 Supplemental Table 4). However, for the MANOVA that included latitude, both range and latitude were significant (
 p < 0.05 in both cases; 
 Supplemental Table 4).
